00:29:21,793 --> 00:29:23,695
Miss Wakura is working towards

491
00:29:23,762 --> 00:29:26,464
the same direction as Mr. Kurokawa
without us realizing it.

492
00:29:26,531 --> 00:29:27,599
Yeah.

493
00:29:28,099 --> 00:29:30,435
I'll go to see the people involved again.

494
00:29:31,936 --> 00:29:33,037
Miss Wakura.

495
00:29:33,571 --> 00:29:36,374
-Mr. Kurokawa, cool down a bit.
-Oh, thank you.

496
00:29:40,545 --> 00:29:41,913
Have some tea, Mr. Yufuin.

497
00:29:44,749 --> 00:29:46,684
"The ghost at the swamp?"

498
00:29:46,751 --> 00:29:47,685
What?

499
00:29:47,752 --> 00:29:50,688
Miss Arima got this letter in June
eight years ago,

500
00:29:50,755 --> 00:29:55,026
when a park was built on the swamp
where the bottle was disposed of.

501
00:29:55,093 --> 00:29:57,128
Did you find something curious?

502
00:29:57,195 --> 00:30:02,100
"I read a news article that says
a park will be built on the swamp."

503
00:30:02,167 --> 00:30:05,703
<i>That reminds me. My daughter</i>
<i>had told me something in the past.</i>

504
00:30:05,770 --> 00:30:08,973
<i>Rumor has it that</i>
<i>there was a ghost at the swamp.</i>

505
00:30:09,040 --> 00:30:11,342
<i>A large shadow floated on the swamp</i>

506
00:30:11,409 --> 00:30:13,711
<i>and you would die if you saw it.</i>

507
00:30:14,279 --> 00:30:16,848
"My daughter was very frightened.

508
00:30:16,915 --> 00:30:19,150
The ghost story is an innocent one,

509
00:30:19,217 --> 00:30:23,154
but I think it will disappear
along with the swamp."

510
00:30:23,655 --> 00:30:25,590
"You die if you see it?"

511
00:30:31,496 --> 00:30:33,198
What's the matter, Miss Wakura?

512
00:30:33,264 --> 00:30:36,000
Mr. Shiobara wrote some notes
when he interviewed the children.

513
00:30:36,067 --> 00:30:37,435
Where are they?

514
00:30:37,502 --> 00:30:40,171
Oh, I think the notebook is on my desk.

515
00:30:43,675 --> 00:30:44,509
Miss Wakura!

516
00:30:44,576 --> 00:30:45,944
Found it!

517
00:30:47,078 --> 00:30:48,379
Have a look at this.

518
00:30:49,581 --> 00:30:52,217
"A crying girl."

519
00:30:52,283 --> 00:30:54,085
Has it got anything to do with that?

520
00:31:11,736 --> 00:31:15,540
Miss Wakura, this could be
important evidence!

521
00:31:18,710 --> 00:31:21,546
If rubbish had been disposed of
around this area…

522
00:31:21,613 --> 00:31:23,248
The swamp is ahead.

523
00:31:24,983 --> 00:31:26,551
I knew it!

524
00:31:26,618 --> 00:31:29,520
The girl saw a ghost because she was here.

525
00:31:29,587 --> 00:31:31,556
The problem is who saw it.

526
00:31:32,523 --> 00:31:34,025
Let's check with Miss Matsugashita.

527
00:31:39,330 --> 00:31:40,865
-Sorry for coming so late.
-Sorry.

528
00:31:40,932 --> 00:31:42,800
What's the matter? I'm busy.

529
00:31:42,867 --> 00:31:46,838
Please tell us about the ghost
at the swamp near the company houses.

530
00:31:46,905 --> 00:31:48,606
-A ghost?
-Well…

531
00:31:48,673 --> 00:31:50,375
When you were in primary school
and the murder happened,

532
00:31:50,441 --> 00:31:52,510
there was a rumor that there was
a ghost at the swamp, right?

533
00:31:53,411 --> 00:31:55,780
It was too long ago and I don't remember.

534
00:31:55,847 --> 00:31:57,015
Wait…

535
00:31:57,081 --> 00:31:59,150
Do you remember the day of the murder?

536
00:31:59,217 --> 00:32:03,087
Didn't a girl who lived in
the same neighborhood tell you that

537
00:32:03,154 --> 00:32:04,956
she saw a ghost at the swamp?

538
00:32:07,492 --> 00:32:10,995
If we know who she is, maybe we can
clear your father's false charges.

539
00:32:12,330 --> 00:32:13,498
What?

540
00:32:15,366 --> 00:32:18,036
Excuse me. Why are we here?

541
00:32:18,102 --> 00:32:20,171
You'll know if you come.

542
00:32:22,473 --> 00:32:23,708
Yumi Haruna?

543
00:32:24,309 --> 00:32:25,476
Reiko?

544
00:32:26,644 --> 00:32:28,046
Why?

545
00:32:28,112 --> 00:32:30,048
They asked me to come here.

546
00:32:30,114 --> 00:32:32,917
We will tell you the details inside.

547
00:32:46,531 --> 00:32:48,299
-The things are ready.
-Okay.

548
00:32:54,305 --> 00:32:57,308
I am sorry about the other day.

549
00:32:59,777 --> 00:33:01,980
Will you explain everything to me now?

550
00:33:02,680 --> 00:33:05,083
What are you going to do here?

551
00:33:06,551 --> 00:33:09,787
What do you think this is?

552
00:33:09,854 --> 00:33:10,888
What?

553
00:33:12,156 --> 00:33:14,759
-Water?
-We reconstructed the swamp.

554
00:33:16,627 --> 00:33:21,833
The swamp one kilometer away,
which is a park now.

555
00:33:21,899 --> 00:33:24,135
What do you do this for?

556
00:33:24,202 --> 00:33:26,170
You'll know when you see it.

557
00:33:26,237 --> 00:33:27,405
Please come with me.

558
00:33:32,343 --> 00:33:35,179
Miss Haruna, please stand here.

559
00:34:10,214 --> 00:34:11,149
Look in front of you.

560
00:34:24,695 --> 00:34:26,397
On the day of the murder,

561
00:34:27,432 --> 00:34:30,601
you saw the same thing as this
at the swamp, didn't you,

562
00:34:31,536 --> 00:34:32,537
Miss Haruna?

563
00:34:33,071 --> 00:34:33,905
What was that?

564
00:34:33,971 --> 00:34:37,675
It is called a Brocken specter.

565
00:34:38,810 --> 00:34:40,211
Brocken specter?

566
00:34:40,812 --> 00:34:43,548
When there is fog on top of a mountain

567
00:34:43,614 --> 00:34:46,751
and strong light is shone from
behind the observer,

568
00:34:46,818 --> 00:34:49,487
<i>water droplets in the air</i>
<i>refracts the light</i>

569
00:34:49,554 --> 00:34:54,892
<i>and forms a rainbow-colored halo</i>
<i>around the observer's shadow.</i>

570
00:34:54,959 --> 00:34:58,262
The phenomenon frightened people
and it was called Brocken-Gespenst,

571
00:34:59,330 --> 00:35:02,433
but actually,
it also occurs on level ground

572
00:35:02,500 --> 00:35:03,901
under specific conditions.

573
00:35:05,103 --> 00:35:08,840
For example, in the evening,
when temperature drops rapidly

574
00:35:08,906 --> 00:35:12,243
<i>and a dense fog forms</i>
<i>on waters like a swamp.</i>

575
00:35:12,310 --> 00:35:15,179
<i>If there is no wind,</i>
<i>other conditions are met</i>

576
00:35:15,246 --> 00:35:17,014
<i>and the light</i>
<i>of the setting sun is strong,</i>

577
00:35:17,081 --> 00:35:19,183
<i>the same phenomenon can be observed.</i>

578
00:35:19,784 --> 00:35:21,285
I'm not surprised that

579
00:35:21,919 --> 00:35:24,489
children would think that
it really was a monster.

580
00:35:26,023 --> 00:35:26,924
The experiment is done.

581
00:35:31,462 --> 00:35:34,265
This is the data of the weather
of the day of the murder.

582
00:35:34,966 --> 00:35:38,369
Temperature dropped rapidly after 4 p.m.

583
00:35:38,436 --> 00:35:44,041
There was only half an hour
after that with no fog and no wind.

584
00:35:45,009 --> 00:35:48,246
The setting sun was shining
on the swamp at that time.

585
00:35:48,312 --> 00:35:51,282
If you had seen the ghost,

586
00:35:51,349 --> 00:35:55,586
it shows that you were at
the rubbish dump at the swamp

587
00:35:55,653 --> 00:35:58,890
from 4 p.m. to 4:30 p.m.,
when all conditions were met.

588
00:35:58,956 --> 00:36:02,426
Wait a minute. Why did you go there?

589
00:36:02,493 --> 00:36:03,895
Miss Haruna.

590
00:36:06,531 --> 00:36:08,499
The report says that
on the day of the murder,

591
00:36:09,400 --> 00:36:13,070
you were at home with your mother
until the party started.

592
00:36:16,107 --> 00:36:17,742
But you actually went to the swamp.

593
00:36:19,977 --> 00:36:22,213
You went there to dispose of the bottle

594
00:36:23,147 --> 00:36:24,682
that contained potassium cyanide.

595
00:36:30,087 --> 00:36:31,088
Yumi?

596
00:36:32,723 --> 00:36:33,925
Is that true?

597
00:36:40,364 --> 00:36:41,532
I am sorry.

598
00:36:44,969 --> 00:36:46,237
Reiko.

599
00:36:48,072 --> 00:36:49,140
I am sorry.

600
00:36:51,475 --> 00:36:53,044
I am sorry.

601
00:36:58,049 --> 00:37:02,954
My mother told me to go there
and dispose of the bottle.

602
00:37:03,020 --> 00:37:05,389
My father was laid off,

603
00:37:05,456 --> 00:37:08,593
<i>then my mother started to work at</i>
<i>Itoe Electric's factory</i>

604
00:37:08,659 --> 00:37:10,261
<i>and we moved to the company's house.</i>

605
00:37:10,761 --> 00:37:15,933
<i>But our family became a mess</i>
<i>because of my violent father.</i>

606
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:21,739
<i>That day, my mother didn't allow me</i>
<i>to join the Christmas party,</i>

607
00:37:21,806 --> 00:37:22,907
<i>but in the evening…</i>

608
00:37:22,974 --> 00:37:27,745
Go and throw this away
at the rubbish dump at the swamp.

609
00:37:27,812 --> 00:37:32,116
After you do this job for me,
you can go to the Christmas party.

610
00:37:33,284 --> 00:37:34,151
Wear gloves.

611
00:37:35,486 --> 00:37:37,154
Make sure you don't touch it directly.

612
00:37:37,221 --> 00:37:42,226
I went to the swamp as I was told
and disposed of the bottle.

613
00:37:44,729 --> 00:37:47,898
It was when I saw the ghost at the swamp.

614
00:37:49,367 --> 00:37:53,037
<i>Then, when I came back,</i>
<i>the murder happened.</i>

615
00:37:53,104 --> 00:37:57,074
<i>My mother probably wanted to kill</i>
<i>my father so much that she did that.</i>

616
00:37:58,576 --> 00:38:03,614
I didn't realize that
I helped her destroy evidence

617
00:38:04,415 --> 00:38:07,551
until after a very long time.

618
00:38:10,154 --> 00:38:11,389
What the heck?

619
00:38:13,557 --> 00:38:17,094
What was the last 24 years
of my life, then?

620
00:38:19,697 --> 00:38:24,302
I wrongly assumed
that my father was a murderer…

621
00:38:25,936 --> 00:38:30,608
and I spent all the time hating him,
until now.

622
00:38:40,818 --> 00:38:42,820
CLOSED HEARING OF APPEAL FOR RETRIAL

623
00:38:42,887 --> 00:38:46,891
My mother worked part-time
for Itoe Electric,

624
00:38:46,957 --> 00:38:50,628
at General Affairs Section,
like Mr. Shikine.

625
00:38:54,065 --> 00:38:56,901
It should be very easy for her…

626
00:38:58,202 --> 00:39:00,871
to get the potassium cyanide.

627
00:39:01,906 --> 00:39:05,643
In other words, you're saying that
your mother, Azusa Haruna,

628
00:39:05,710 --> 00:39:07,712
was the culprit
who poisoned the champagne?

629
00:39:07,778 --> 00:39:11,182
Why did you keep quiet about this?

630
00:39:11,982 --> 00:39:13,017
I…

631
00:39:17,088 --> 00:39:18,756
I felt guilty about this…

632
00:39:20,124 --> 00:39:22,960
but I swept it under the carpet.

633
00:39:24,128 --> 00:39:29,166
My mother passed away
ten years after the murder.

634
00:39:30,167 --> 00:39:31,168
And…

635
00:39:33,337 --> 00:39:39,243
I tried to convince myself that
the case was over.

636
00:39:41,212 --> 00:39:42,146
Also…

637
00:39:43,681 --> 00:39:46,283
I thought it would be okay
if I kept quiet.

638
00:39:49,553 --> 00:39:50,855
For my mother's sake,

639
00:39:52,223 --> 00:39:57,561
I thought I shouldn't let anyone know
about the crime we committed.

640
00:39:59,864 --> 00:40:01,465
We know your story clearly now.

641
00:40:02,032 --> 00:40:05,202
We will have a careful discussion
about this case again

642
00:40:05,269 --> 00:40:07,471
and inform you our decision later.

643
00:40:08,939 --> 00:40:12,443
We hope you would give this
a very serious consideration.

644
00:40:14,578 --> 00:40:16,847
Because the witness statement
is very clear.

645
00:40:16,914 --> 00:40:20,851
The court will decide whether
the statement is clear or not.

646
00:40:26,257 --> 00:40:27,324
Your Honor.

647
00:40:29,527 --> 00:40:32,396
May I say a few words before we finish?

648
00:40:32,930 --> 00:40:33,931
Go ahead.

649
00:40:42,706 --> 00:40:44,141
The reason that…

650
00:40:45,309 --> 00:40:48,712
Miss Yumi Haruna came today
to make this painful statement

651
00:40:50,080 --> 00:40:51,115
is because…

652
00:40:53,517 --> 00:40:55,820
she cares about Mr. Shikine
and his daughter.

653
00:40:59,824 --> 00:41:02,026
She can't let them remain
a death row inmate

654
00:41:03,294 --> 00:41:06,263
and the daughter of a death row inmate.

655
00:41:09,533 --> 00:41:12,603
The incident happened 24 years ago.

656
00:41:14,505 --> 00:41:20,478
Maybe many people in the world
have already forgotten about the case,

657
00:41:20,544 --> 00:41:22,446
<i>but Mr. Shikine</i>

658
00:41:23,214 --> 00:41:25,950
<i>and his daughter Reiko</i>
<i>have never forgotten about it.</i>

659
00:41:27,084 --> 00:41:29,353
Mr. Shikine wants help now.

660
00:41:32,323 --> 00:41:36,760
Reiko is suffering because of
the false charges against her father.

661
00:41:41,899 --> 00:41:45,669
Mr. Hiromitsu Shikine is innocent.

662
00:41:47,137 --> 00:41:50,975
Even though he cannot take back
the 24 years he lost,

663
00:41:52,176 --> 00:41:54,278
taking away the future he has…

664
00:41:56,213 --> 00:41:57,948
would be unforgivable.

665
00:41:58,516 --> 00:42:00,384
Please don't be biased by
the wrong conviction in the past

666
00:42:02,953 --> 00:42:05,389
and make a decision based on the truth.

667
00:42:08,025 --> 00:42:09,460
We strongly hope you would do so.

668
00:42:12,363 --> 00:42:14,965
SEVERAL DAYS LATER

669
00:42:15,032 --> 00:42:16,267
I took it out!

670
00:42:17,401 --> 00:42:19,236
<i>The next story.</i>

671
00:42:19,303 --> 00:42:21,272
<i>An appeal for a retrial</i>

672
00:42:21,338 --> 00:42:24,742
<i>of the Itoe Electric Company House</i>
<i>Murder Case 24 years ago</i>

673
00:42:24,808 --> 00:42:27,611
<i>was dismissed by the court.</i>

674
00:42:27,678 --> 00:42:28,879
Dismissed?

675
00:42:28,946 --> 00:42:30,814
The locked door

676
00:42:30,881 --> 00:42:34,552
didn't open this time too.

677
00:42:34,618 --> 00:42:36,387
This is what happened.

678
00:42:37,187 --> 00:42:38,556
It's disappointing.

679
00:42:41,158 --> 00:42:44,628
"The appeal for a retrial is dismissed."

680
00:42:45,296 --> 00:42:46,497
The reason is,

681
00:42:46,564 --> 00:42:49,667
"No new evidence found
has been clear enough

682
00:42:49,733 --> 00:42:53,837
to declare appellant innocent."

683
00:43:04,715 --> 00:43:06,250
It's so bitter!

684
00:43:26,770 --> 00:43:27,938
Reiko.

685
00:43:45,756 --> 00:43:46,824
Reiko?

686
00:43:53,864 --> 00:43:54,865
Are you Reiko?

687
00:43:56,033 --> 00:43:57,067
Dad.

688
00:43:58,335 --> 00:43:59,169
I…

689
00:44:01,572 --> 00:44:02,773
I am sorry!

690
00:44:07,277 --> 00:44:09,346
It must have been tough for you.

691
00:44:12,449 --> 00:44:13,617
Dad!

692
00:44:16,487 --> 00:44:17,855
I am sorry!

693
00:44:20,791 --> 00:44:24,628
I'm sorry that I couldn't trust you.

694
00:44:27,598 --> 00:44:28,699
I am sorry.

695
00:44:40,611 --> 00:44:42,479
You have grown up.

696
00:44:46,650 --> 00:44:47,484
Reiko.

697
00:44:49,987 --> 00:44:51,055
Reiko.

698
00:44:56,660 --> 00:44:57,628
Reiko.

699
00:45:11,208 --> 00:45:12,943
COURTHOUSE

700
00:45:33,063 --> 00:45:35,999
THE DRAMA IS FICTITIOUS

701
00:45:36,066 --> 00:45:37,501
THE FINAL CHAPTER

702
00:45:37,568 --> 00:45:39,870
<i>A murder that is very similar</i>
<i>to the one 11 years ago.</i>

703
00:45:39,937 --> 00:45:41,472
<i>I want to investigate thoroughly</i>
<i>and defend you.</i>

704
00:45:41,538 --> 00:45:43,440
<i>The two separations that came.</i>

705
00:45:43,507 --> 00:45:44,575
Maybe it can be settled.

706
00:45:44,641 --> 00:45:46,376
Who killed her, then?

707
00:45:46,443 --> 00:45:48,579
<i>I think I can share your pain.</i>

708
00:45:48,645 --> 00:45:51,014
-<i>Mr. Kurokawa!</i>
-<i>Miss Wakura!</i>

709
00:45:51,081 --> 00:45:53,417
I never wanted to kill anyone!

710
00:45:53,484 --> 00:45:56,587
<i>The murderer is another person</i>
<i>and they incriminated someone.</i>

711
00:45:56,653 --> 00:45:59,089
<i>Maybe probatio diabolica is possible.</i>

712
00:45:59,156 --> 00:46:00,657
<i>If he really was innocent,</i>

713
00:46:00,724 --> 00:46:02,860
I wish he hadn't killed himself
and stayed alive.

714
00:46:02,926 --> 00:46:05,462
You don't know how cold a dead body is.

